<h1 id='faq'>FAQ</h1><h2 id='how-to-find-serum-market-address'>How to find Serum market address?</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to https://dex.projectserum.com</li>
<li>Select the appropriate exchange pair in the top left corner</li>
<li>Click the little (i) button next to the pair name</li>
<li>Copy the address</li>
</ol>
<h2 id='how-to-find-token-mint-address'>How to find token mint address?</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to https://solscan.io/</li>
<li>In the search box start typing the desired token name, eg ATLAS</li>
<li>Select the right token &amp; hit enter</li>
<li>You will be taken to the <a href="https://solscan.io/token/ATLASXmbPQxBUYbxPsV97usA3fPQYEqzQBUHgiFCUsXx">token&#39;s page</a>, which contains the address</li>
</ol>
<h2 id='what-is-a-mango-account'>What is a Mango account?</h2>
<p>In Mango, each user can have multiple isolated sub accounts all owned by their PublicKey. 
These accounts are referred to as Mango accounts, and the accounting for their deposits, borrows, and open positions is done independently of other Mango accounts.
If you&#39;re not sure which mango account you want to access, or it is your first time using Mango, use &#39;0&#39; for the mangoAccountNumber. 
To read more about Mango accounts take a look at <a href="https://docs.mango.markets/development-resources/mango-client-api#mango-accounts">Mango&#39;s documentation</a>
The easiest way to fetch Mango accounts for a user is to use the <a href="https://github.com/blockworks-foundation/mango-client-v3/blob/e2d0d67b63f943b6dbf7cc40e6e06c6986f2aa1c/src/client.ts#L1726">Mango client</a></p>
<h2 id='how-to-find-saber-swap-address'>How to find Saber swap address?</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to <a href="https://app.saber.so/#/pools/">Saber&#39;s website</a></li>
<li>Select the appropriate swap pair</li>
<li>Scroll down to the Account Info section</li>
<li>Copy the &quot;Swap Account&quot; address</li>
</ol>

<p>Alternatively, the <a href="https://registry.saber.so/">Saber Pool Registry</a> contains up to date pool information.</p>
